text: In spite of the lackluster quality of the entire film, Underworld Awakening I actually enjoyed the direction it took. How it shifted the conflict from vampires and lycans by including humans as an even more significant threat. Based on the trailer I'd say this element has been removed. Also as fun as it may be to watch, Selene has virtually achieved godhood. In the previous films yes she acquired enhanced abilities by diablorie however she was shown to still struggle, which I do not imagine seeing in blood wars. I fail to for see anywhere for the story to progress beyond this film. The genre has truly been overplayed and tapped to the point of it being a dry vein. I plan on watching this as a final farewell to the Underworld saga. I'd love to see the creative forces behind it consider telling stories about other supernatural creatures.

text: The *Underworld* franchise is always going to be unique to me.  It's one of the very few _Vampire/Lycan_ stories that don't try to insult my intelligence.  The visuals and designs are really great.  The characters learn over time and adapt.  There's actually an *origin* story that seems plausible and antagonists that aren't stupid; having a legit reason why they're doing what they're doing. [_case-in-point_, *Lucian*] - *Kraven* was an asshole, but at least he was a cleverly deceitful one.  Now, the only thing I'm interested in, are Michael and Eve.  Why create something amazing then just ignore it?  It doesn't make sense, considering it's important for Selene too.  Think about it, Selene could potentially become an *Elder* for a new generation of Vampires.  She's the bridge for the Old and New; their daughter Eve and Michael could then become the Leaders of the Coven.  You could call it, "The New Covenant".  I'm still not sure about the Lycans yet, I'd have to think about it.

text: The only reason this franchise still goes on (in a more and more predictable and stupid way) is because Kate Beckinsale was Len Wiseman's wife. Come on. In every movie, no matter how insanely powerful and evolved her foes (remember Quint?!) are, she always finds some kind of secret power/blood/ability to kill them. It's going to be exactly the same with this latest installment. No matter how powerful you get, there's always going to be someone more powerful than you, eventually. text: Just finished watching this movie and must point out the 3 major crucial things it lost:   1) It lost its storyline. Underworld always had a very detailed build up in regards to storyline plot. Everything would eventually unravel as the movie carried on. Like it has for the 1st 3 movies. Now it was just mostly filled with needless action scenes. Like every 10 or so minutes they were in another battle. It was just mainly blood and gore and this movie didn't stand on its own.  2) Another thing I loved about Underworld was its racial and cultural diversity. Yet in this version it lacked that heavily. The only thing you got close to in diversity was people pretending to be Elves from Lord of the Rings. Before like in the 1st 3 movies. It really detailed the landscapes as well as the people inhabiting it. This version just used poorly revised old gimmicks and sequences shown from prior movies.  3) It lost is Gothica feel. Before you felt immersed in its world. It had a heavy Gothica feel to it. Now its literally under shows like Shadowhunters(which I find terrible) meets Vampire Diaries(which I also detest). Shows like The Originals would easily outclass this movie and it uses far less violence. The movie lost its tranquil feel. It had a more futuristic approach to movies like *Interview with the Vampire*; which I loved. Yet now it's just Rambo with light bullets and mystical elves.   I kid you not. When you watch this. You'll see they just rewashed all the major scenes from prior version of the movie into this one. Yet they failed terribly at doing so.   I'll just stick with the 1st 3 movies and pretend like I never saw these last 2.  Franchise probably should of died on a high note after *Rise of the Lycans*. Yet they ruined a great thing by dragging it on like *The Matrix* and *Blade*.
